the skies gleam metallic, the terrain desolate,
devastation pervades the landscape's stark state;
a feeble stream lingers on mud-caked ground,
where salt springs bubble and quagmires resound;
the darling river laments its futile embrace,
struggling against drought, losing its race;
attempting to nourish the land far and wide,
yet thwarted by drainage and nature's dry tide;
dreaming of bustling banks, verdant scenes,
children playing, life flowing through its means;
but only bleached bones and demons remain,
mocking the river's perpetual, desperate strain.

london, thou art of towns the absolute best.
sovereign of cities, most beautiful and bright,
of great fame, wealth, and royal might;
of lords, barons, and noble knights so right;
of delightful, lovely ladies shining light;
of famous clerics in their formal call;
of merchants powerful and strong in height:
london, thou art the flower of cities all.

rejoice, thou lustrous troy novaunt,
city once called new troy of old,
imperial on earth, as thou dost flaunt,
princess of towns, of pleasure untold,
no christian king holds wealth to unfold;
for manly power and natural craft's thrall,
none fairer since noah's flood did roll:
london, thou art the flower of cities all.

